LIMPOPO cops arrested seven suspects in connection with a cash-in-transit heist in Polokwane on Monday. It's alleged the suspects made off with an undisclosed amount of money, after they used explosives to blow-up the cash van. ALSO READ:Â WATCH: DRAMATIC CASH HEIST! "On Monday an unknown group of suspects ambushed a cash delivery truck on the Matlala road, just outside Polokwane and made off with an undisclosed amount of money," Hawks spokesperson Captain Matimba Maluleke said. Maluleke said a manhunt resulted immediately and seven suspects aged between 24 and 49 were arrested since Monday and the early hours of Tuesday morning in different parts of the province. According to Maluleke during the operation cops recovered two stolen vehicles with false registration plates, ammunition, money bags and explosives. All suspects are expected to appear in the Polokwane Magistrate Court on Wednesday facing numerous charges. Over the past month there have been at least ten cash-in-transit heists across the country.